My remark about dropping the raw content wasn't related to error handling - sorry for being too vague here. I was referring to your suggestion of changing the return value from
let status = resp.status();
let content = resp.text().await?;
if status.is_success() {
    let entity: Option<UsersSetRegularSuccess> = serde_json::from_str(&content).ok();
    let result = ResponseContent { status, content, entity };
    Ok(result)
} ...
to this:
let status = resp.status();
if status.is_success() {
   Ok(resp.json().await?) // .map_err(Error::Reqwest) should not be necessary
} ...
With this, status and content will no longer be provided to the API user in case of success. I do not know why this might be necessary or useful - however, it is provided by the current version of the code for some reason.

